            <b>1.Engagement (Nischitartham):</b>
                The official journey of the couple begins with this ceremony, where families exchange gifts, and an auspicious wedding date is announced by the family priest. A Ganesh Pooja is performed for divine blessings.
            <b>2.Pendikoothuru (Haldi Ceremony):</b>
                Both bride and groom are smeared with turmeric and oil paste, symbolizing purification and prosperity.
            <b>3.Snathakam:</b>
                At the groom’s home, this ritual signifies his readiness for marital responsibilities, where he dons a silver thread as a mark of transition into domestic life.
            <b>4.Kashi Yatra:</b>
                A playful ritual where the groom pretends to renounce worldly desires and pursue a spiritual path. The bride’s brother convinces him to marry, symbolizing the importance of family life.
            <b>5. Vundavalli Ceremony (Reception of the Groom’s Family)</b>
                In some regions of Andhra Pradesh, there is a ritual called the Vundavalli Ceremony which is a reception ceremony specifically for the groom’s family. It takes place at the bride’s home before the wedding, where the groom's family is formally welcomed with traditional offerings of sweets, fruits, and gifts. This ritual fosters a sense of connection and warmth between the two families before the wedding.
        </pre>
