            <b>1.Bride’s Entry:</b>
                Traditionally, the bride is escorted to the mandap by her uncles, often carried in a bamboo basket.
            <b>2.Jeerakalla-Bellamu:</b>
                A ritual where the bride and groom, separated by a curtain, apply a paste of cumin and jaggery on each other’s hands, symbolizing life’s bittersweet nature.
            <b>3.Mangalasutra Ceremony:</b>
                The curtain is removed, and the groom ties the sacred mangalasutra around the bride’s neck, tying three knots that signify mental, physical, and spiritual unity.
            <b>4.Saptapadi and Kanyadanam:</b>
                The couple exchanges garlands and takes seven sacred steps (Saptapadi) around the fire, each representing vows of love, loyalty, and mutual respect.
        </pre>
