        <h2>Agricultural Tradition in Andhra Pradesh</h2>
        <p>
            Agriculture has been the backbone of Andhra Pradesh's economy for centuries, and it continues to play a significant role in shaping the state's culture, lifestyle, and traditions. With a diverse climate, fertile soil, and extensive river systems, Andhra Pradesh has a deep agricultural heritage, influencing its festivals, rituals, and way of life. Here’s an overview of the agricultural traditions in the state:
        </p>
        <h3>1. Farming Practices and Crops</h3>
        <p>Agriculture in Andhra Pradesh is primarily rain-fed, with irrigation being crucial in many parts of the state. The state is home to both food crops and cash crops, with traditional farming methods being passed down through generations. The major crops grown in Andhra Pradesh include</p>
        <pre style="display: block;        
        margin-top: 1em;      
        margin-bottom: 1em;  
