        line-height: 1.2;        
        color: inherit;           
        font-family: inherit;">
         <b>1.Rice:</b> Known as the “rice bowl of India,” Andhra Pradesh is one of the largest producers of rice in the country. Paddy farming is especially common in the delta regions of Krishna and Godavari rivers.
         <b>2.Groundnut (Peanut):</b> The state is also a leading producer of groundnuts, primarily in the Rayalaseema region.
         <b>3.Cotton:</b> Andhra Pradesh is a major producer of cotton, especially in the districts of Guntur, Warangal, and Khammam.
         <b>4.Tobacco:</b> The state is famous for its high-quality tobacco, grown predominantly in the districts of Prakasam, Guntur, and Khammam.
         <b>5.Sugarcane:</b> Grown widely across the state, sugarcane is integral to the sugar industry and its by-products.
         <b>6.Fruits and Vegetables:</b> Andhra Pradesh also grows a variety of fruits, including mangoes, bananas, papayas, and citrus fruits, along with a wide range of vegetables.
         <b>7.Spices:</b> The state is also known for its production of chili peppers, turmeric, and ginger, making it a key player in the spice industry.
            

        </pre>
        <h3>2. Agricultural Tools and Techniques</h3>
        <p>In the past, farmers in Andhra Pradesh relied on traditional farming tools such as ploughs, bullocks, and manual labor. However, with modernization, mechanized equipment like tractors, seed drills, and harvesters have become common. Despite the advancements, many farmers in rural areas still practice organic farming and rely on natural fertilizers like cow dung, compost, and neem-based products.</p>
        <h3>3. Festivals Linked to Agriculture</h3>
        <p>Agriculture and farming are at the heart of many festivals celebrated in Andhra Pradesh. These festivals mark important agricultural milestones such as the sowing, harvesting, and worship of deities for bountiful crops.</p>
        <pre style="display: block;        
        margin-top: 1em;      
